# Frontend React / TypeScript

- Use functional components and React hooks only.
- Keep presentational components simple; avoid heavy business logic in UI components.
- Type props explicitly with TypeScript (`type` preferred).
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks (`useSomething`) instead of duplicating it.
- Centralize API calls in dedicated services instead of page components.
- Handle `loading`, `error`, and `empty` UI states explicitly.
- For components with behavior, add focused React/Vitest tests based on outcomes, not implementation details.
